    "monster": true,
    "notes": "50kg Beast (Trapper), underground or forest walker, #App: 1d6, Treasure: Incidental. Fangs (1d6+3); armor 1; walk 10m/action; Morale DM-1. A giant variant of a black widow, this arachnid is a horror to behold. May walk on walls and ceilings; may \"rappel\" down a string of web to long distances. Advantage to Surprise checks due to its ability to lurk anywhere. Webbing: Characters who fight giant spiders may get caught in their webbing. If the spider attacks from ambush, Roll DEX 8+ each round to avoid being caught in webbing. Characters who are caught in webbing cannot move and attack at -2 penalty. It requires 1d6 fire or slashing damage to free a character from a web. Characters may break free from webbing on a STR 10+ throw. Venom: 8+/3d6 toxin. (Instinct 8, Pack 5)",
